author: Georgi Kantchev
title: Copper Prices Pressured by Stronger Dollar
text:
LONDON—Copper prices fell on Wednesday, along with other industrial metals, on a stronger dollar and continuing negative sentiment in the commodities market.
Three-month copper on the London Metal Exchange fell 0.3% to $5,183.50 in midmorning European trade.
